Facts, figures and records at the French Open Tennis  Championships which open here Monday:
WINNERS OF MOST SINGLES TITLES
Men: 6-Bjorn Borg (Sweden) 1974, 1975, 1978, 1979, 1980, 1981
Women: 7-Chris Evert (USA) 1974, 1975, 1979, 1980, 1983, 1985, 1986
WINNERS OF MOST CONSECUTIVE TITLES
Men: 4-Bjorn Borg (Sweden) 1978-1981
Women:3-Helen Wills-Moody (USA) 1028-1930, Hilde Sperling (Germany)  1935-1937, Monica Seles (Yug) 1990-1992
WINNERS OF MOST DOUBLES TITLES
Men's doubles: 6-Roy Emerson (Australia) 1960, 1961, 1962, 1963, 1964, 1965
Women's doubles: 7-Martina Navratilova (USA) 1975, 1982, 1984, 1985, 1986,  1988, 1987
WINNERS OF MOST TITLES (all events)
Men: 9-Henri Cochet (France) 1926-1932 (4 singles, 3 doubles, 2 mixed  doubles)
Women: 13-Margaret Smith-Court (Australia) 1962-1973 (5 singles, 4  doubles, 4 mixed doubles)
WINNERS OF BOTH JUNIOR AND SINGLES TITLES
Men: (5) Ken Rosewall (Australia) Junior-1952, Senior-1953, 1968: Roy  Emerson (Australia) Junior-1954, Senior-1963, 1967: Andres Gimeno (Spain)  Junior-1955, Senior-1972: Mats Wilander (Sweden) Junior-1981, Senior-1982,  1985, 1988: Ivan Lendl (USA) Junior-1978, Senior-1984, 1986, 1987
Women: (3) Francoise Durr (France) Junior-1960, Senior-1967: Mima Jausovec  (Yugoslavia) Junior-1973, Senior-1977: Hana Mandliklova (Czech) Junior-1978,  Senior-1981
